post_text:
We have joined the GoodSchoolsRoc online application starting December 1, 2019!

As a public school, The Genesee Community Charter School is open to all applicants who fit our age guidelines. Students entering Kindergarten must turn 5 years old on or before December 1st. Students are admitted to the Genesee Community Charter School through a random lottery in April of each year. Families of prospective students must submit an online application on GoodSchoolsRoc.org by Wednesday, April 1, 2020 to be entered in the lottery.

Please note: Our school calendar is different from the Rochester City School District and suburban districts.

Rock, Paper, Scissors Results:

In a friendly competition, demonstrating the highest level of sportsmanship, 1st Grade dethrones 6th grade and takes the trophy to their classroom!

And, in the first annual staff competition, Arts Team representative, Mrs. Lockner, takes the grand prize! She is picture below wearing the beautiful winner's robe and crown holding the trophy!

Great job GCCS!
